			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Hard LDoN Advice<a name="49685"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 2 04 9:35 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Howdy Folks!
<br />

<br />
Wiladancer here from the Torv Server, hoping, yet once again, to pick the brains of you wonderful folks. I have read the &quot;Pulling Hard LDoN&quot; guide here and thank you for that. I do need to fine tune what I am doing and this may be a rather long post, so please bear with me.
<br />

<br />
I finally got Fading Memories and our adventuring group decided we'd try a Hard LDoN last night.
<br />

<br />
To set the stage, I'm a 64th Bard, not very well dressed as I am a casual player in a family guild. I do not have my Epic although I am working on that as well. Group makeup last night was:
<br />

<br />
64 Bard (that would be me)
<br />
2x 65 Paladin's
<br />
64 Monk
<br />
65 Cleric
<br />
63 Warrior
<br />

<br />
My duties were initially:
<br />

<br />
Puller
<br />
Haster
<br />
Slower
<br />
CCer
<br />

<br />
Initial Songs Memmed:
<br />

<br />
Lull - Silent Song of Quellious
<br />
Debuff - Occlusion of Sound
<br />
Amp - Amplification
<br />
Resist/DS - Psalm of Veeshan
<br />
Overhaste - Rizlona's Call of Flame
<br />
Haste - Warsong of Zek
<br />
Slow - Requiem of Time
<br />
Mez - Dreams of Terris
<br />

<br />
Current Mods:
<br />
Battle Drummer's Main-Gauche - Percussion 2.0
<br />
Troubador's Mace - Brass 1.8
<br />
Painted Primal Mask - Stringed 1.4
<br />
Gravestone of Dire Melodies - Wind 1.6
<br />

<br />
Mana Pool allows for 2.5apx FM's
<br />

<br />
Mistmoore LDoN Halls of Sanguitary something or rather
<br />

<br />
The initial pulls consisted of 3 on the first lull resist, then 3 on the second lull resist. These were fought at zone in and we prevailed, albeit long battles as I had to keep 2 mezzed and positioned so landed RoT and sang WoZ. So the first room of 6 went well, considering the lack of room for FM.
<br />

<br />
We then moved in to the room and I proceeded to the next room. 3rd Pull was yet another resist and brought 3 with me. Same deal, mezzed 2 and had to try and keep PoV up with WoZ. We lost one Pally, then I had a ton of resists on my mez, even with OOS. Down goes the other Pally, then Warrior, then Monk. Cleric zones, then I run to zone and get out with 22% (thank you RUN3).
<br />

<br />
We rez, med and then do the Monk/Bard tag routine, which worked very well for the next 6-7 pulls. At this point, I am switching out tunes as we lost our Shammy buffs and many folks in group have vs Undead procs. 
<br />

<br />
Out with the Lull, in with the Katta's Song of Sword Dancing. This seems to add to the critical hits and procs, but our MT is taking quite a beating now. I then drop OOS for Niv's Melody of Preservation. This does help a bit for damage mitigation, but now I have to battle through the additional resists (why can't we have more songs at our disposal). 
<br />

<br />
The monk died on one overpull from a nasty DoT. I then died a bit later from an overpull of 4, hit FM, but got hit at the same time and must have been an undead somewhere in there. 
<br />

<br />
All in all, we lost the adventure due to the partial wipe, additional deaths and a LD moment. We were fairly close though. 
<br />

<br />
I also found, on our last pull, that Chain mezzing seemed to work great for singles. Anyone else use this?
<br />

<br />
I would love to hear your thoughts, questions and criticism. I have learned oh so much from these boards and do thank you in advance for all your continued education.
<br />

<br />
Wila...
<br />
</span></td>
