			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hard LDoN Advice<a name="49695"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 2 04 9:59 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Assuming you are getting slow to land consistently, the damage shield isn't really a critical part of your DPS as a group.  And if your sense is that the main tank is taking too much damage and over-burdening your healers, the answer despite what some will tell you, is NOT HP regen.  It's boosted AC.  Niv's Harmonic is your friend in hard LDON if your main tank is less than 1600 AC or so.  It can help you take less damage on that residual agro, too.  Seriously, the added AC of that song is superior to HP regen from other songs.  Warsong is a must if you need the haste -- POV is a must if you are dealing with a lot of casters and Mistmoore has a lot.  But Niv's Harmonic went into my lineup about the second hard LDON I tried and stayed there.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443370">Steppy Astravox</a><br>
Code of Silence<br>
