				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hard LDoN Advice<a name="49704"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 2 04 10:24 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Also if you get to the ones where they are hitting for 900+ a 63 warrior will not cut it.  Hard LDoN's are controlled by two things.  The pulling/cc (2-3 mobs and tank is dead unless doing furious till you land mezzes) and how good your tank is.  In a normal 65 hard generally I will not take any tanks that are not in an elemental guild unless I know them or have a spot healer and shammy (do pick up groups quite a bit).
<br />

<br />
If the pallies where chain stunning, that would be a good way to reduce damage.  Didn't have a snarer besides you either, which is not a good thing, esp. in EC.  
<br />

<br />
But there are tons of threads on how too pull and what to do in a hard ldon.  Would suggest you read them.  You really shouldn't have been pulling if doing everything else and you had a (decent) monk, since lull is worthless in a hard till you hit 250+ cha and if you died it would probably mean a wipe (no slow or CC besides root parking).  
<br />

<br />
Also if you are the only slower i would recomend having mischief memmed for when when RoT is resisted (recast time).  </span></td>
