				<td colspan="2"><span>Two things first of all...
<br />

<br />
1) For a Bard to be the only slower, you need an Elem+ tank and a good cleric with decent heal AA and manapool.
<br />

<br />
Remember that our slow is &quot;only&quot; 54% and thus the tanks eat an extra 21% damage compared to a shaman slow. Getting hit for 9xx's by Hard LDoN mobs, those 21% add up to alot quickly.
<br />

<br />
2) When you are lulling (i prefer to call it pac'ing tho) in Hard LDoN's, your Cha should be at least 200+. Mine is at 240 unbuffed, and I sometimes end up having as many as 7 resists in a row before the paci takes hold.
<br />

<br />
To counter that, keep your Solons Charismatic Concord ready.
<br />

<br />
As for song setup...
<br />

<br />
Regular twist...
<br />

<br />
1. Winds of Marr
<br />
2. Warsong of Zek
<br />
3. Call of the Muse
<br />
4. Psalm of Veeshan
<br />

<br />
Backup songs....
<br />

<br />
5. Requiem of Time
<br />
6. Silent song of Quellious
<br />
7. Solons Charismatic Concord
<br />
8. Lullaby of Morell.
<br />

<br />
I use the Requiem to pull after I paci'd. Also pulling with slow means less damage on YOU if the tank dont grab aggro fast.
<br />

<br />
As far as paci'ing goes, I heard some say that mobs wont aggro on your resisted paci if you arent in their line of sight. I havent tested this out much, I just know you can have loads of resisted paci's without aggro, and other times they jump you right away both while facing me and not facing me.
<br />

<br />
For paci'ing, its all about charisma and a bit of luck on the resist check the mobs get. But hey, FM is there if you get a crappy pull so no sweat &quot;)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
