				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">For a Bard to be the only slower, you need an Elem+ tank and a good cleric with decent heal AA and manapool. 
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I won't argue that it is certainly easier to do Hard LDON with this combination.  I would not call it necessary.  My regular group started doing hard LDONs about 6 or 7 months ago.  We just killed Rallos last weekend and we have never hunted Ssra Basement or Vex Thal -- which gives you an idea of our gear.  So our warrior is not elem+ and our regular group doesn't even have a cleric -- druid and shaman.  Yes, most of the time, that means we have shaman slows, but we have endured pulls many times with just my slows for whatever reason and I can assure you that while it slows the team down a tad, it really doesn't make it impossible by any stretch of the imagination.  The max hit damage in hard LDON -- 992 -- can be survived easily by non-elemental tanks IF they have decent defensive AAs like maxed CA/CS and some LR and ID to add onto it.  That is also why I strongly recommend Niv's Harmonic.  Increasing your tank's AC by 60+ (80+ if I remember to keep Harmonize going) is going to cut down noticeably on damage taken.</span></td>
