			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hard LDoN Advice<a name="49738"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 2 04 12:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I heard some say that mobs wont aggro on your resisted paci if you arent in their line of sight</span></blockquote>
<br />
Sadly, this isn't the case :(
<br />

<br />
I think you did really well to nearly win the adventure given the group makeup. Pulling hards is not easy, and a good tank and healer is required; I don't think I've ever done a hard adv with myself as the main slower, haster and cc person.
<br />

<br />
I'd echo the sentiments on making use of the monk's unresistable lull. One lull is sufficient to reduce 90% of pulls down to 2 mobs. Those few times it takes a bit more, you've got the monk's FD, your fade, mezz, snare etc to shake off the extras.
<br />

<br />
Make sure you leave room between yourself and the group; a popular tactic is to mezz adds, run to group with the one or two left over, and then fade - so the mezzed mobs return to their spawn spots. Its essential your group understands this, an SK/necro doing a group lifetap or a healer spot-healing you on inc will lead to a wipe.
<br />

<br />
One thing I find hard to decide is song lineup on hards. Normal is pretty standard but with a hard, more compromises are required.
<br />

<br />
My basic lineup is probably:
<br />
1. PoV
<br />
2. Muse
<br />
3. Marr
<br />
4. Zek
<br />
5. HoS
<br />
6. RoT
<br />
7. Lull
<br />
8. Mezz
<br />

<br />
PoV - DS is nice, but more for resists as hard ldon mobs can really hurt you with dots and nukes.
<br />
Muse - Great dps boost, hard to miss this one out
<br />
Marr - Great for both mana and hp regen
<br />
Zek - DS, Atk, and if no chanter/shaman then more haste
<br />
5-8 are self-explanatory.
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately there are 2 gaps in this (at least!)
<br />
a) Niv's Harmonic. AC boost really helps - but is it worth sacrificing any of 1-4 for this? I'd consider dropping Zek if there's somebody else covering haste but I'm not sure it out-weighs anything else.
<br />
b) Snare. Snare is really useful for making more controlled pulls. Normally I rely on someone else snaring runners as I'll be off pulling before the old mob is dying. Again, I can drop Zek for this in some groups, the other option is to drop RoT but I really like the added safety of pre-slows with RoT - the slow on snare is significantly less and of course short duration too, not to mention it doesn't work on unsnareables. 
<br />
c) If charisma is low, you might want to throw in our charisma song. Goodness knows where you fit it in though ;)
<br />

<br />
Last adventure I dropped RoT and used snare/slow in its place; this seemed to work quite well with a chanter slowing.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
