			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hard LDoN Advice<a name="49804"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 2 04 6:01 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Remember that our slow is &quot;only&quot; 54% and thus the tanks eat an extra 21% damage compared to a shaman slow. Getting hit for 9xx's by Hard LDoN mobs, those 21% add up to alot quickly. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Every single mob in a hard LDON mitigates slow, though you won't see the mitigation message if you have a brass mod of 2.4 or more - I think that's the bug, anyway.
<br />

<br />
That cuts the slow difference down to about 17%, and since you're slowing on inc, not trying to land Malos and THEN slow after the mob is already in camp, your tank is fighting a slowed mob for its entire life, not just the last 2/3rds of it.
<br />

<br />
Bard &gt; Shaman for slows in hard LDoN.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
