				<td colspan="2"><span>I've only pulled 3 LDON Hards (2 EF and 1 EC), 2 wins, 1 loss, and the loss really should of been a win. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I found Lull to be a pretty effective tool in EF with either Shaman/Enchanter CHA buff and CHA song.  I found Lull to be a very ineffective tool in EC regardless of CHA.
<br />

<br />
I totally agree with everyone else on the use of RoT.  I found that when lull pulling, tagging the MOB with Harmony and then following up with RoT worked great.
<br />

<br />
One thing I feel I need to get better at is judging how far back to leave my group.  Too much distance is bad.  Too little distance is bad.
<br />

<br />
I also think I need to get better at judging which mobs will come on the pull, so that I have when I mez/snare, I have simply have to toggle to get the 2nd mob targeted on a possible 4 pull.
<br />

<br />
I also need I think I need to get better at using my song messages to feel what is happening rather than always having visual contact.
<br />

<br />
1) Do most of you start singing your song, turn away to face your party and then start running after the song lands?  I tend to have a bad habit I think of facing the pull, and backing up while singing.
<br />

<br />
2) Does anyone ever use dispell as a pull tool?</span></td>
