<br />
1st mistake...you were puller and just about everything else.
<br />
-have monk pull and have your assist set to him.  Tag teaming is a great way to pull hards and it allows you to OOS or HOS on incoming...thus giving you a better chance at landing slows.
<br />

<br />
2nd mistake was pointed out...you just can't rely on lull on the hard advs.  Learn the pathing of the adv and learn to remove lull as a pulling tool, trust me, you'll learn why later on in advanced stages of EQ.
<br />

<br />
3rd mistake also pointed out...for Hards, always boost the tanks AC with Nivs and do your best to get your casters VOQ prior to entering the adv... I rarely play Chorus during a Hard adv unless we have a downtime due to death.
<br />

<br />
LDoN Hards a great way for Bards to learn pulling techniques and I highly recommend them to everyone.  The normal advs are so dull you can pretty much charge a room and survive intact.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
