				<td colspan="2"><span>I was totally embarassed in an EC (SRO) LDON the other night.  Mez pulling is not something I have had to use in the past, so still learning the ins and outs of its use.  The big issues I had were:
<br />

<br />
<u>MOB Speed</u>
<br />
I only have Run3.  Mobs run SOOOO fast.  My usual pulling method has always been to pull, see what comes, if it looks ok, turn around and take to group, if not, backpeddle and mez another one or two, turn around, run and fade.  I just can't do this in EC Hards.  I don't have the time to turn around, at least if I pull with a short range song like mez.
<br />

<br />
<i>(I am using Terris, 100 foot range.  I hadn't realized it, but Morrell has a 200 range.  This could solve a lot of my problems with being &quot;too&quot; close for mez pulling)</i>
<br />

<br />
I am thinking that I am going to have to &quot;blind&quot; pull.  Since a lot of people seem to favor singing mez for the pull, I would:
<br />

<br />
1) target 2 mobs.
<br />
2) Start singing mez, turn around
<br />
3) When song lands, run
<br />
4) Switch targets, sing mez.
<br />

<br />
When you have both mobs mezzed, bring what remains back to the group. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />   I could fade, turn around and see what I brought, but it may be that those 2 were the only ones coming on the pull, so it would be a wasted fade (I only have FT5)
<br />

<br />
The other option I guess, is to make the group leave the dungeon when my SoE fades, reapply it, and then re-enter.
<br />

<br />
<u>Mez Aggro Range</u>
<br />
The aggro range on mez seems to be quite small.  That is, mez a mob.  Say you only get 1 aggro.  Mez this aggro.  Wait for the 1st mez to wear off.  The 1st mob and 2 others will come.
<br />

<br />
So, when ever I use mez to pull, it appears to me that I am forced to fade, because, I REALLY don't know if I will get 1 or 4 mobs when it wakes up.
<br />

<br />
<u>Aggro Messages</u>
<br />
I don't seem to be able to rely on the aggro messages.  Sometimes when I see 2 aggro messages, I may end up getting 4 mobs.
<br />

<br />
<u>Chase Range</u>
<br />
Hard LDON mobs don't seem to have a limit on their chase range.  Meaning, I can mez a mob, run 18 seconds out of range, and it will still chase me down.  I had assumed that LDONS worked a lot like the outside world and that if you run outside some chase range, they gave up, but would reaggro if you entered back into chase range.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Questions:
<br />

<br />
- Until I get Morrell, I am thinking a better strategy than mez pulling would be to sing my longest range, lowest aggro generating song, perhaps the lvl 40 cancel magic song?
<br />

<br />
- How much of an effect does range have on Lull resists?  I think I am going to test out this idea.
<br />

<br />
- How much of an effect does line of sight have on Lull resists?  I think I am going to test out this idea.
<br />
</span></td>
