				<td colspan="2"><span>I have heard people say that range and los have effect on lull resists.  My personal experience -- over 100 LDONs, most of them hard -- is that there is no consistent improvement from breaking LOS and lulling at longer range. For mez pulling, a lot of times I move into a room invis or I send an eye (I use stalking probes - sold my SS Helm two years ago and never bought another one) pick a target and have the tank assist me.  Then I pick two other targets and load them into the toggle buffer.  Then I mez one and run back to camp landing mez on the other as I go.  At this point, you have one mezzed at the original room, one mezzed halfway back, and one, or maybe two, heading to your camp.  I then fade, remez the one halfway back, and take care of any adds in camp.  Makes a room of 4 very doable in hard LDON.  I forget the name of the spell shaman have -- it makes the mob sneeze violently and move back out of melee range and be stunned for a few seconds.  Our regular group includes a shaman who makes liberal use of that spell to help out in crowd control and it is wonderful.</span></td>
