				<td colspan="2"><span>In our Dual Pally Group, we have a rather adept gent who ghetto cc's via root parking. He also saves my tail regularly by healing my tinfoil bard suit ladened butt. 
<br />

<br />
I have seen some really great advice, but it looks as though I need to do quite a few things before I alone can successfully pull a complete hard LDoN. 
<br />

<br />
1st - CHA, mine is way to low to make a difference at this point. I am not fond of sacrificing AC for CHA, nor am I enticed by the idea of losing a song slot to CHA tune.
<br />

<br />
2nd - FT items, I have none. I can Fade at most 2-3 times during and adventure. This just won't do it.
<br />

<br />
3rd - Most rooms have 6+ MoBs in it. Nothing to sneeze at, unless you're a Shammy and they do run d*mn fast. I need to be able to better separate them. 3 or 4 to split or park? fairly easy to do. With 6 and no fade, you might as well send the Freeport Press your obituary.
<br />

<br />
I guess it comes down to, practice makes perfect. I will have my monk friend pull more often so that we can do a bit more in the tagging department. I like the idea of a 2-pull feign then mez tag, prep SA Pally with Mez message. Toggle the incoming and nail with RoT and bring to MA Pally, attack target from angle so you can see Mezzed one coming in door. Have it root parked. If resist, mez, OOS, reland Root and focus on the first in camp. 
<br />

<br />
Maybe once I get my epic, this will become a tad easier as I might have a song or two more to play with. 
<br />

<br />
Thank you everyone for your thoughts. You really bring out the best in us.
