			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hard LDoN Advice<a name="51448"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 12 04 2:39 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote"> I forget the name of the spell shaman have -- it makes the mob sneeze violently and move back out of melee range and be stunned for a few seconds.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Virulent Paralysis - it's a 3 level AA ability that costs 3/3/3.  It's a knockback and root, but unfortunately doesn't have a stun component.  It's DR based so you can root things that are very MR, the glimmer drake models in ToV come to mind here.
<br />

<br />
It has a 2 minute refresh time, and at level three lasts just slightly longer than 2 minutes so you can keep something permanently placed if it's not particularly DR.
<br />

<br />
It knocks back something in the direction the shaman is facing at the time it lands, so you can do some neat positioning tricks.  It's good for getting clerics to stand up, all that sitting down they do isn't good for the circulation so parking a mob on them is really quite beneficial.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
